In a message dated 9/3/2002 10:07:27 PM Pacific Daylight Time, cjay(-at-)well.com 
writes:
> Go to Sears, and buy their 1.5 ton ($30) small floor jack, and while you're 
> there, get two nice jackstands too. I did this 12 years ago, and everything 
> still works great, and the jack is small enough to disappear under the bed. 
> 

Hi Volks,
That is definitely the way to go!  Not only can you change flat tire, but you 
can R&R the engine/clutch, & even the tranny if need be.  We made a cradle 
out of wood to put the jack on to keep the wheels off the floor in the bus to 
keep it from rolling around!
Eric&Barb

